	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Apparently you're supposed to desolder (no 'i'; pronounced dee-sod-er) the ROM chips and solder in DIP sockets. Then you can just unplug and replug when you want to change the program.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
